title: Nominalism
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

[[Universals]] don't exist, they're just ideas used to label [[Particulars]].

Similar to [[Realism]], but universals become ideas that we create in our minds to categorize, describe, and understand particulars. Universals have no real existence in the material world.
